snippet.textDisplay: If true, I'm perfectly fine with AMD killing Radeon VII to release a higher-end, Navi-based GPU sooner rather than later. Obviously they'll want the 5700 & 5700XT to sell some decent figures first (both reference and partner cards), I get that. I just hope it offers a similar price to performance to power efficiency ratio as it sounds like the 3700X does, for gaming. It doesn't even need to increase performance over Radeon VII (let alone reach 2080Ti levels). The same 1440p performance numbers as Radeon VII at a much less power hungry usage than Radeon VII or NVIDIA equivalent GPUs is what I'm personally waiting for.
